{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-page","disabled":true,"settings":{}},"f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Caring for your Cotton"}},"template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"enlarge_text":false,"text":"<p>We design our cotton pieces to last, that is why it is so important to look after them. With the right care and attention, your NOVO cotton pieces will be a staple piece for years to come.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-0","template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-1"],"settings":{"align_text":"center","narrow_column":true,"divider":false}},"a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c":{"type":"slideshow","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c-1667561124a81e7b1c-0":{"type":"image","settings":{"top_subheading":"","title":"","title_size":40,"subheading":"","link":"","link_text":"","link_2":"","link_text_2":"","color_accent":"rgba(0,0,0,0)","text_align":"vertical-center horizontal-center","image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Cotton_Banner.webp","parallax_direction":"top","overlay_opacity":0,"focal_point":"center center"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c-1667561124a81e7b1c-0"],"settings":{"section_height":"550px","mobile_height":"auto","parallax":false,"style":"bars","autoplay":true,"autoplay_speed":5}},"c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Our Guide To Caring For Cotton"}},"template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"enlarge_text":false,"text":"<p>01.<\/p><p>Cotton can be either machine or hand washed but to keep garments from shrinking and keep them looking their best, wash at 30.Â <\/p><p>02.<\/p><p>We advise keeping washing to a minimum so pre-treat small stains where possible to avoid a full wash. <\/p><p>03.<\/p><p>Do this by dabbing a small amount of stain remover on the area. For darker colours we advise patch testing on the inside of the seam to check the colour won't be affected.<\/p><p>04.<\/p><p>When machine washing, place cotton items in a mesh bag to help prevent snagging or twisting.<\/p><p>05.<\/p><p>Hang cotton out to dry as this saves energy, as heat from tumble dryers can cause shrinkage.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-0","template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-1"],"settings":{"align_text":"center","narrow_column":true,"divider":false}},"6cdb4a11-f84e-44bb-a5f3-336c3128122c":{"type":"featured-collection","settings":{"title":"Shop Cotton","home_featured_products":"cotton","per_row":5,"rows":1,"mobile_scrollable":true,"view_all":false,"divider":true}},"29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433-16675625010eb8cfaa-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"enlarge_text":false,"text":"<p><a href=\"\/pages\/garment-care\" title=\"Garment Care\"><strong>Back to Garment Care Guides<\/strong><\/a><\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433-16675625010eb8cfaa-1"],"settings":{"align_text":"center","narrow_column":true,"divider":false}}},"order":["main","f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0","a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c","c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd","6cdb4a11-f84e-44bb-a5f3-336c3128122c","29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433"]}